        "Ingredient": "inventory_item",
        "Ingredient Name": "inventory_item",
        "Category": "menu_category",
        "Unit": "inventory_unit",
        "UOM": "inventory_unit",
        "Unit of Measure": "inventory_unit"
      },
      "gotchas": [
        "Toast 'Net Sales' is already after discounts and comps \u2014 do NOT subtract comps again.",
        "Toast labor exports are a SEPARATE report from sales; they will arrive as different CSVs and must be joined on Business Date + Location.",
        "Toast 'Sales Category' is the reporting group, which may differ from the kitchen menu category.",
        "Multi-location Toast accounts sometimes export one file per location with no location column \u2014 the location is in the filename.",
        "A column labeled 'COGS' is usually TOTAL COGS (food+beverage+paper), not Food Cost alone \u2014 map to total_cogs and confirm before using as food cost.",
        "Voids (rung-but-not-made) are tracked separately from Comps/Discounts (made-and-given). Map 'Void Amount' to voids, not comps.",
        "Toast labor arrives at SHIFT grain (per employee, per clock-in) in a separate file from sales \u2014 aggregate to location-week and join on Business Date + Location."
      ]
    },
    "square": {
      "label": "Square",
