        "Total Paid Overtime": "direct_labor",
        "Variation": "modifier",
        "SKU": "item_id",
        "Quantity": "quantity_sold",
        "Gross Sales (Item)": "item_revenue",
        "Net Sales (Item)": "item_revenue",
        "Discounts (Item)": "comps",
        "Modifiers Revenue": "modifier_revenue",
        "Square Feedback Rating": "guest_satisfaction"
      },
      "gotchas": [
        "Square 'Transactions' = checks/tickets, NOT covers. Square does not natively track guest count \u2014 per-person metrics must fall back to per-check.",
        "Square 'Net Sales' = Gross Sales - Discounts - Comps - Refunds; tax is separate.",
        "Square labor data comes from Square Shifts/Payroll, a different export with columns like 'Total Paid' and 'Regular Hours'.",
        "Square exports often split into separate 'Items', 'Categories', and 'Sales Summary' files \u2014 they must be reconciled.",
        "A column labeled 'COGS' is usually TOTAL COGS (food+beverage+paper), not Food Cost alone \u2014 map to total_cogs and confirm before using as food cost.",
        "Voids (rung-but-not-made) are tracked separately from Comps/Discounts (made-and-given). Map 'Void Amount' to voids, not comps.",
        "Square raw exports are a FLAT TRANSACTIONAL stream (one row per payment) and use 'Date'+'Time' \u2014 derive Business Date via business_day_close_hour and roll up to location-week BEFORE computing KPIs.",
        "'Total Collected' = Net Sales + Tax + Tips. NEVER treat as net_sales \u2014 it inflates revenue. Always parse down to Net Sales."
      ]
    },
